On the demand and market-flow side, several pieces describe divergent dynamics across exchanges and a Coinbase-driven impulse supporting recovery. Cointelegraph notes that Bitcoin inflows diverged, with selling pressure easing on Binance while Coinbase exhibited more dominant activity, suggesting a shift in where liquidity and interest are flowing. A separate Cointelegraph piece highlights a Coinbase-led surge in spot volume that helped absorb weekend selling pressure and pull price back toward a notable level, underscoring how exchange- and venue-driven demand can meaningfully affect intraday momentum. In the institutional-flow arena, Strategy appears to have overtaken BlackRock’s IBIT in Bitcoin holdings after bear-market buying activity, signaling a shift in ownership concentration and tactical positioning within large-cap players, as reported by CoinDesk. Conversely, a development around the Strategy fund’s STRC—slipping below its par value—was framed by Cointelegraph as a potential catalyst for reduced buying this week, raising the risk of near-term downside pressure if support from such instruments wanes.

